ce indicators for the Legislature to use in determining whether the credit is achieving its stated goal shall be the number of taxpayers allocated a credit pursuant to this section or Section 23692, and the total dollar value of credits allocated.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) (A) The State Office of Historical Preservation shall, no later than June 1, 2028, and annually thereafter, submit a report to the Legislature, in compliance with Section 9795 of the Government Code, stating the number of taxpayers allocated a credit, and the total dollar value of credits allocated.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) The disclosure requirements of this paragraph shall be treated as an exception to Section 19542.</div></i></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(o) <font color="#B30000"><strike>(1)<span class="EnSpace"/></strike></font>This
